    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>September 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date>.</p>
            <p>Reverend Sir,</p>
            <p>In consequence of the advertisement<lb/> of the Hebrew Ed. Society of your<lb/> city
                I have this day directed a letter<lb/> to <persName>Mr. I. Binswanger</persName>, in
                which<lb/> I reported him on the course of studies<lb/> I pursued, the testimonials
                I hold<lb/> and how long, where and in what<lb/> occupation I spent the time of
                my<lb/> sojourn in this country.</p>
            <p>After taking the liberty of referring<lb/> also to you, Rev. Sir, I applied for<lb/>
                the vacant situation, mentioned in<lb/> the above advertisement, provided<lb/>
                stipulations and salary be acceptable.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Now, Rev. Sir, I know the great<lb/> authority you exercise and the
                great<lb/> influence you have with the Board<lb/> of the above school. I
                likewise<lb/> flatter myself to be known to</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>you as fully worthy of filling the<lb/> above situation to the entire
                satis-<lb/>faction of the Board and community.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Would you therefore interfere in<lb/> my behalf and recommend me
                for<lb/> the above situation?</p>
            <p>I know your noble character and<lb/> the interest you take in the promotion<lb/> of
                our sacred religion too well, as<lb/> to entertain for one moment the<lb/> fear,
                that the little literary con-<lb/>troversy we had last year which<lb/> was of a
                strictly private nature and<lb/> did not spread into publicity<lb/> would induce
                you, not to exert your<lb/> influence in my and our sacred<lb/> religion's favor,
                for you assuredly<lb/> know that capable men are quite<lb/> scarce in this
                country.</p>
            <p>I have not the least doubt that<lb/> I cannot only in my sphere as a</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>teacher of the above school, but also<lb/> as a contribution to orthodox
                journals<lb/> on religious questions and matters be<lb/> of salutary influence.</p>
            <p>Hoping you will comply with my<lb/> request and wishing you <add>כוח"ט כתיבה וחתימה
                    טובה</add> with<lb/> all my heart, I am, Rev. Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">yours most obediently</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">L. Buttenwieser</persName>
            </p>
            <p>My direction is:</p>
            <p><persName role="author">L. Buttenwieser</persName>,</p>
            <p>care of <persName>Messrs Heller Bros &amp; Co.</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati O.</placeName>
            </p>
